I placed my order in at 3:25pm, with the expectation that the order would be out for delivery at 5:00pm. I had the tracker up on my computer, and the first update was at 4:30pm, when the pizza was being prepped. At 5:05pm, there was still no further update, so I decided to call the restaurant, to see if I could get an update on the order status. When I called, I was asked if I could hold for a minute, which I was happy to do. I was then on hold for eight minutes. While on hold, the tracker finally updated from the prep to bake status at 5:07pm. It then was updated from the bake to quality check status at 5:12pm. When I finally got on the phone with someone, I had mentioned that the status of the order had been updated while I was on the phone, but I asked for a reason why it was so delayed. The person on the phone would not provide me with a direct answer, instead saying “we have your order, do you have any other questions.” I tried to ask more questions, but was cut off and told the same line from before: “we have your order, do you have any other questions.” Finally, I caved and just said no, and the person on the other end of the line hung up without saying anything else. As I have ordered from this location previously without incident, I was shocked at how awful the customer service was for this particular order. I understand that it is snowing, and that they might be backed up, but I was not happy with the lack of response or apology when I was simply asking for an update on my order. I waited another 35 minutes, without the status of my pizza order changing, so I decided to call the restaurant again. I was placed on hold immediately. While on hold, the order finally changed from “quality check” to “out for delivery” at 5:50pm. After six minutes on hold, I decided to hang up the phone, because I knew the delivery person would be arriving shortly, and wanted to make sure I didn’t miss them buzzing my apartment, since I am at this point starving. The pizza finally arrived at my apartment at 6:04pm. I’ve never had an experience from Domino’s like this ever, and I might have to reconsider where I order pizza from in the future.
